scam_incident_description:
I received an SMS from +6591748846 claiming to be from DBS, stating that there was a failed payment attempt. 
It requested that I verify my identity via a provided link (https://secure-dbs-login.com/verify) to prevent unauthorized transactions. 
After clicking the link, I was directed to a website resembling DBS's official website, where I provided my my banking credentials. 
Subsequently, my credentials were used to increase my account transfer limit, resulting in an unauthorized transaction to a DBS. 
The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $2001.75 was made to DBS account 31918039 on 2025-04-13.
scam_specific_slots: {'scam_subcategory': 'SMS BANK PHISHING', 'scam_impersonation_type': 'LEGITIMATE ENTITY', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity': 'DBS', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity_name': 'DBS', 'scam_phished_details': 'BANKING CREDENTIALS', 'scam_use_of_phished_details': 'INCREASE TRANSFER LIMIT', 'scam_pretext_for_phishing': 'PAYMENT FAILED'}

scam_incident_description:
I saw an ad for discounted food items on Facebook posted by 'glamb'. The seller was promoting the sale of durians.
Upon clicking the link (https://www.deals4u-3244.shop/durians) in the post, I was redirected to a site requesting my my card credentials to complete the purchase. 
After submitting my details, I received an SMS requesting to key in my Youtrip login code. I subsequently received an SMS that there had been a log in to my account from another device. 
Later, an unauthorized transaction was made to a MAYBANK. The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $588.87 was made to MAYBANK account 53760605 on 2025-07-07.
scam_specific_slots: {'scam_subcategory': 'SOCIAL MEDIA AD FOOD PHISHING', 'scam_impersonation_type': 'NA', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity': 'NA', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity_name': 'NA', 'scam_phished_details': 'CARD CREDENTIALS', 'scam_use_of_phished_details': 'LOG IN FROM ANOTHER DEVICE', 'scam_pretext_for_phishing': 'DISCOUNTED FOOD ITEMS'}

I saw an ad for discounted food items on Facebook posted by 'cynthia45'. The seller was promoting the sale of durians.
Upon clicking the link (https://www.deals4u-7036.shop/durians) in the post, I was redirected to a site requesting my my card credentials to complete the purchase. 
After submitting my details, I received an SMS requesting to key in my Youtrip login code. I subsequently received an SMS that there had been a log in to my account from another device. 
Later, an unauthorized transaction was made to a DBS. The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $1190.86 was made to DBS account 63541974 on 2025-01-04.

scam_incident_description:
I received an SMS from +6593893000 claiming to be from DBS, stating that there was outstanding bills that needed to be paid. 
It requested that I verify my identity via a provided link (https://secure-dbs-login.com/verify) to prevent unauthorized transactions. 
After clicking the link, I was directed to a website resembling DBS's official website, where I provided my my card credentials. 
Subsequently, my credentials were used to increase my account transfer limit, resulting in an unauthorized transaction to a MAYBANK. 
The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $2103.80 was made to MAYBANK account 46874123 on 2025-05-23.

I received an SMS from +6591763794 claiming to be from DBS, stating that there was unauthorized access to my bank account. 
It requested that I verify my identity via a provided link (https://secure-dbs-login.com/verify) to prevent unauthorized transactions. 
After clicking the link, I was directed to a website resembling DBS's official website, where I provided my my banking credentials. 
Subsequently, my credentials were used to increase my account transfer limit, resulting in an unauthorized transaction to a HSBC. 
The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $253.39 was made to HSBC account 94250492 on 2025-05-23.
scam_specific_slots: {'scam_subcategory': 'SMS BANK PHISHING', 'scam_impersonation_type': 'LEGITIMATE ENTITY', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity': 'DBS', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity_name': 'DBS', 'scam_phished_details': 'BANKING CREDENTIALS', 'scam_use_of_phished_details': 'INCREASE TRANSFER LIMIT', 'scam_pretext_for_phishing': 'UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS TO BANK ACCOUNT'}

Upon clicking the link (https://www.deals4u-1492.shop/durians) in the post, I was redirected to a site requesting my my banking credentials to complete the purchase. 
After submitting my details, I received an SMS requesting to key in my Youtrip login code. I subsequently received an SMS that there had been a log in to my account from another device. 
Later, an unauthorized transaction was made to a MAYBANK. The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $1233.59 was made to MAYBANK account 07484202 on 2025-05-14.
scam_specific_slots: {'scam_subcategory': 'SOCIAL MEDIA AD FOOD PHISHING', 'scam_impersonation_type': 'NA', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity': 'NA', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity_name': 'NA', 'scam_phished_details': 'BANKING CREDENTIALS', 'scam_use_of_phished_details': 'LOG IN FROM ANOTHER DEVICE', 'scam_pretext_for_phishing': 'DISCOUNTED FOOD ITEMS'}

scam_incident_description:
I received an SMS from +6594465623 claiming to be from DBS, stating that there was a failed payment attempt. 
It requested that I verify my identity via a provided link (https://secure-dbs-login.com/verify) to prevent unauthorized transactions. 
After clicking the link, I was directed to a website resembling DBS's official website, where I provided my my card credentials. 
Subsequently, my credentials were used to log in to my account from another device, resulting in an unauthorized transaction to a MAYBANK. 
The transaction is as follows:
A transaction of $1896.94 was made to MAYBANK account 69439540 on 2025-07-02.
scam_specific_slots: {'scam_subcategory': 'SMS BANK PHISHING', 'scam_impersonation_type': 'LEGITIMATE ENTITY', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity': 'DBS', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity_name': 'DBS', 'scam_phished_details': 'CARD CREDENTIALS', 'scam_use_of_phished_details': 'LOG IN FROM ANOTHER DEVICE', 'scam_pretext_for_phishing': 'PAYMENT FAILED'}

scam_incident_description:

scam_incident_description:
I received a call from an individual named Sandy Goh, claiming to be a bank officer from DBS. He had contacted me using +6597182454.
He informed me of suspicious or fraudulent transactions detected in my bank account and asked me to confirm these transactions. 
When I denied knowledge of such transactions, the call was transferred to another individual named Inspector Thomas Lee via WhatsApp, claiming to be from the Monetary Authority of Singapore. 
They accused me of involvement in legal investigation and demanded that I transfer my bank funds to a "safety account" to assist with the investigations. 
Inspector Thomas Lee showed me his warrant card during the process and I believed him. I complied and transferred the funds, resulting in the following transaction:
A transaction of $1944.36 was made to DBS account 32236770 on 2025-05-21.
I later realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable. I subsequently verified the situation with the bank and Singapore Police Force through official channels and 
there were no records of Sandy Goh and Inspector Thomas Lee.
scam_specific_slots: {'scam_subcategory': 'BANK AND SPF IMPERSONATION', 'scam_impersonation_type': 'GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity': 'DBS', 'scam_first_impersonated_entity_name': 'SANDY GOH', 'scam_second_impersonated_entity': 'MONETARY AUTHORITY OF SINGAPORE', 'scam_second_impersonated_entity_name': 'INSPECTOR THOMAS LEE'}

I received a call from an individual named Jeremy Tan, claiming to be a bank officer from UOB. He had contacted me using +6598144388.
He informed me of suspicious or fraudulent transactions detected in my bank account and asked me to confirm these transactions. 
When I denied knowledge of such transactions, the call was transferred to another individual named Inspector Royston Wong via WhatsApp, claiming to be from the Monetary Authority of Singapore. 
They accused me of involvement in money laundering and demanded that I transfer my bank funds to a "safety account" to assist with the investigations. 
Inspector Royston Wong showed me his warrant card during the process and I believed him. I complied and transferred the funds, resulting in the following transaction:
A transaction of $2283.96 was made to MAYBANK account 09306727 on 2025-01-14.
I later realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable. I subsequently verified the situation with the bank and Singapore Police Force through official channels and 
there were no records of Jeremy Tan and Inspector Royston Wong.

scam_incident_description:
I received a call from an individual named Sandy Goh, claiming to be a bank officer from UOB. He had contacted me using +6597110864.
He informed me of suspicious or fraudulent transactions detected in my bank account and asked me to confirm these transactions. 
When I denied knowledge of such transactions, the call was transferred to another individual named Inspector James Tan via WhatsApp, claiming to be from the Monetary Authority of Singapore. 
They accused me of involvement in money laundering and demanded that I transfer my bank funds to a "safety account" to assist with the investigations. 
Inspector James Tan showed me his warrant card during the process and I believed him. I complied and transferred the funds, resulting in the following transaction:
A transaction of $114.99 was made to BOC account 33548929 on 2025-06-13.
I later realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable. I subsequently verified the situation with the bank and Singapore Police Force through official channels and 
there were no records of Sandy Goh and Inspector James Tan.

scam_incident_description:
I received a WhatsApp call from an individual named Michael Lee, who claimed to be from the Ministry of Manpower. He had contacted me using +6593788514. 
He claimed that workers employed under my details were involved in money laundering. 
When I denied knowledge of these workers, the call was transferred via WhatsApp to a second individual named Inspector Timothy Lee, claiming to be from the Singapore Police Force. 
He instructed me to transfer money to a bank account to support the investigations. As I was scared, I complied with his requests. As a result, I made the following transaction:
A transaction of $47910.19 was made to CITIBANK account 21804144 on 2025-06-25.
I realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable. I also verified the situation with the Ministry of Manpower and Singapore Police Force, 
where there were no records of Michael Lee and Inspector Timothy Lee.
